==English==
===Adjective===
'''pop-up'''
# coming into [[view]] suddenly from a [[concealed]] position
# opening out to form a [[three-dimensional]] structure when the [[page]] of a [[book]] is opened

===Noun phrase===
'''pop-up''' (''plural'': pop-ups)
# something that pops up
# a pop-up [[advertisement]]
#{{baseball}} A [[ball]] that has been hit to a considerable height above the [[infield]] or the shallow [[outfield]]

